Here is an example of a ZenStack MCP server tool that queries a database with nested relations:
tsx
const users = await db.user.findMany({
  select: {
    id: true,
    name: true,
    posts: {
      // Relation-level filter
      where: {
        tags: { some: { name: "typescript" } },
      },
      select: {
        id: true,
        title: true,
        tags: {
          // Deep filter
          where: { name: "typescript" },
          select: { name: true },
        },
        comments: {
          where: {
            body: { contains: "great" },
          },
          // Switch to include here — we want all Comment columns
          include: {
            author: {
              select: { id: true, name: true },
            },
          },
        },
      },
    },
  },
});

This query demonstrates how ZenStack's ORM allows traversing nested relations, but it also highlights the 'context bloating' issue due to the large schema generated.
